Background

		Mr. Thomas J. Marusak, also known as Tom, is Founder of Comfortex Corporation and serves as its President. Mr. Marusak serves as the Chairman of New York's Capital Region Center for Economic Growth. In 1997, he was appointed by Governor George Pataki and then confirmed by the New York Senate as a Director for the New York State Energy and Development Authority and continues to serve on its board. He has also represented the interests of small/medium size manufacturing ... businesses of New York as a delegate at the White House. He serves as a member of the Advisory Board of Directors for Key Bank of New York, Dynabil Industries Inc., Clough Harbour Associates Technology Services Company of Albany. Mr. Marusak has been a Director of MTI MicroFuel Cells Inc. (MTI Micro), a majority-owned subsidiary of Mechanical Technology Inc. since October 31, 2005. Mr. Marusak has been a Director of Mechanical Technology, Incorporated since December 16, 2004 and served as its Lead Independent Director since June 11, 2014 until November 10, 2016. Mr. Marusak received a B.S. in Engineering from Pennsylvania State University and an M.S. in Engineering from Stanford University.Read Full Background




